'''
Fitting Alignment Solution
'''

'''
A fitting alignment between two strings consists of a local alignment of an entire smaller strings against
a maximally scoring substring of a larger string. This is performed by initiating the entire first column of
a scoring matrix as zeros and weighting all other edges with appropriate indel/mismatch penalties or positive
matching scores. When backtracking from the maximally scoring node from the last column, this ensures the 
entire smaller string is included in the alignment and that alignment begins at an optimal position where
the first character of the smaller string occurs in the larger string.
'''


